speech.p:
I move:
That Seanad Éireann agrees with the recommendation of the Committee on Procedure and Privileges that, in accordance with the provisions for the address to Seanad Éireann by Distinguished Persons, Ms. Anne Brasseur, President of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe, be invited to address Seanad Éireann on 12th June, 2014 and the following arrangements shall apply: (i) the proceedings at such address shall commence at 12 noon and shall consist of a speech by the Cathaoirleach welcoming President Brasseur, the address by the President at the conclusion of which she will reply to questions from Group Leaders and a speech of thanks by the Leas-Chathaoirleach for the address;
(ii) the proceedings shall conclude no later than 1 p.m.”
